" constellations than \"VPC trio\"\r\n\r\nA possible fix: increase the timeout value?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>The monitoring of GL state is not reliable on some machines: the messages alternates between</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-python\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"n\">X</span> <span class=\"ow\">and</span> <span class=\"n\">GL</span> <span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Not</span> <span class=\"n\">running</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>and</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-python\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"n\">X</span> <span class=\"ow\">and</span> <span class=\"n\">GL</span> <span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">running</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>The affected machine's hability to run Gazebo does not seem hampered.</p>\n<p>This seems to happen more often on \"simulator\" constellations than \"VPC trio\"</p>\n<p>A possible fix: increase the timeout value?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": null, "state": "resolved", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2013-02-07T21:26:52.896178+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2013-03-13T16:08:41.749934+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 28}